'''Paladins''' are [[monster]]s located in [[East Ardougne]]. They require level 70 [[Thieving]] to [[pickpocket]], granting 152 [[experience]], 80 [[coins]] and 1 [[Chaos-Rune]] per pickpocket. A large group of Paladins can be found in a small room on the second floor of [[King Lathas|King Lathas']] [[Ardougne Castle|castle]] but to access the room again level 70 Thieving is required.

== Underground Pass ==
Three paladins are also encountered during the [[Underground Pass]] quest. They must be killed for the insignia they carry which allows deeper access into the dungeon.

==Locations==
* Throughout [[East Ardougne]]
* Second floor of [[Ardougne Castle|King Lathas' castle]] (requires level 70 thieving)

== Appearance ==
The Paladins of Ardougne are light skin toned men with short yellow hair and a yellow beard. He is wearing an [[Adamantite Plate Mail Body]] with[[Adamantite Plate Mail Legs| Adamantite Plate Mail Legs.]] He is wielding an [[Adamantite Mace]] and holding what appears to be either an [[Adamantite Kite Shield]] or [[Adamantite Square Shield]].

